message.text: how to push and commit a new folder in github

parts.text: how to push and commit a new folder in github

response.value:
To commit and push a new folder to GitHub, follow these steps in your terminal:

1. Add the new folder and its contents to git:
```bash
git add <folder-name>
```

2. Commit the changes with a message:
```bash
git commit -m "Add new folder <folder-name>"
```

3. Push the commit to your GitHub repository:
```bash
git push origin main
```

Replace `<folder-name>` with your actual folder name. This will upload the new folder and its files to your GitHub repository.
